Currently, there is no mechanism for Confluence Administrator to check on data like :
 * how many email has been sent out from Confluence

h3. Summary
Rest api call doesn't work correctly when the page title starts with numbers

h3. Environment
Confluence 5.10.8

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create a page and name it "test"
# Run this call: {code:borderStyle=solid} curl -u admin:admin -s -n http://localhost:8090/rest/api/content/search?cql=title=test | python -mjson.tool{code}
# Call returns correct result 
# Now create a page and call 100test
# Run this call: {code:borderStyle=solid} curl -u admin:admin -s -n http://localhost:8090/rest/api/content/search?cql=title=100test | python -mjson.tool{code}

h3. Expected Results
You should get a result of the search since the page exist.

h3. Actual Results
You get a 400 error like the following
{code:borderStyle=solid}
{
    "data": {
        "authorized": false,
        "errors": [],
        "notSuccessful": true,
        "successful": false,
        "valid": true
    },
    "message": "Unrecognised clause at : test",
    "statusCode": 400
}
{code}
 

h3.Workaround
Encode the " when running the query to look like this {code:borderStyle=solid}
curl -u admin:admin -s -n http://localhost:8090/rest/api/content/search?cql=title=%22100test%22 | python -mjson.tool
{code}

