h3. Description

When we try to copy an image from Windows Photo Viewer and then paste that image in Confluence, sometimes it throws an error:

 !pastedImage.png|thumbnail! 

h3. Environment
 - Windows 10
 - Confluence 6.0.3
 - Firefox 50.1.0
 - Windows Photo Viewer

h3. Steps to reproduce:
 # Open an image on Windows photo viewer;
 # Right-click -> Copy;
 # Open a Confluence page in edit mode;
 # Right-click -> Paste;

*Expected result:*
The image is attached properly.

*Actual Result*
"Length of stream must be greater than 0."

*Workaround*
Use Google Chrome;

or

1. Paste and save the image with any image editor;
2. Attach the file itself rather than a selection (via drag and drop, Insert Files button, etc);

